text.tspan: Disease burden from injuries. Disease burden is measured in DALYs (Disability-Adjusted Life Years). DALYs are
used to measure total burden of disease - both from years of life lost and years lived with a disability. One DALY
equals one lost year of healthy life.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease
